        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks CD for influence used with Hooker to obtain a colonial position. Has offended J. H. Balfour by refusing the Darjeeling post and James McNab has become unfriendly, although his experiments do not detract from his garden work.</p> 
<p>Will write <hi rend="italic">Primula</hi> paper for Linnean Society as CD suggests.</p> 
            <p>His Darwinism is unpalatable at Edinburgh Botanic Garden.</p> 
<p>Describes results with non-dimorphic <hi rend="italic">Primula</hi> species. Such cases do not accord with CD’s view that characters are slowly acquired.</p> 
            <p>Thanks for criticism of his writing style.</p>
        </abstract>
